Before using a step, read the matching `reference/steps-{group-slug}.md` file for attributes, child elements, and examples. Group slugs use lowercase with hyphens (e.g. `Rest_Api` ŌåÆ `rest-api`).

## XML conventions

Always use these namespaces on the root `<testData>` element:

```xml
<testData xmlns:s="http://autox.yukthitech.com/steps"
          xmlns:wrap="http://xmlbeanparser.yukthitech.com/wrap"
          xmlns:f="http://autox.yukthitech.com/functions">
```

## Rules

- Every `<testCase>` must have a `name` attribute (no `#`), a `<description>`, and at least one step or validation.
- Use `s:` prefix for steps (e.g. `s:rest-invoke-post`, `s:ui-click`, `s:assert-equals`).
- Use `wrap:steps` and `wrap:validations` to group steps when helpful.
- Data provider iteration data: `${attr.{providerName}.field}`.
- REST response body: `attr.response`; status code: `prop: attr.result.statusCode`.
- UI locators: `type:value` format (e.g. `id: button`, `xpath: //input[@name='fld']`).
- End tests with at least one validation/assertion.
- UI suites should include `<cleanup><s:ui-quit-session/></cleanup>` at suite level.

